  "abstract": "In a method, system, and computer readable medium for distributing messages in a network environment, a message distribution system receives, from a device of a first user who is a follower of the second use, a selection of a plurality of communications endpoints for receiving messages from the second user. The system stores the selection in a storage. The system later receives, from a device of the second user, a message for distribution to one or more unspecified recipients. The system identifies the followers of the second user (including the first user) as recipients of the message, and identifies the plurality of communications endpoints selected by the first user. The system then sends the message to the followers of the second user, including the first user, sending including sending the message to each of the plurality of communications endpoints selected by the first user.",
  "description_link": "https://serpapi.com/searches/685146cc00a1978dd1e42dcf/google_patents_details/description.html",
  "claims": [
    "1. A method of message distribution, comprising:\na. receiving, from a first computing device of a first user, a selection of a plurality of communication options for receiving messages, wherein the first user is one of a plurality of users who are subscribers of a second user; b. storing the selection of the plurality of communication options in a storage; c. receiving, from the first user, subscriber information indicative of one or more other users to be followed by the first user; d. storing the subscriber information in the storage; e. receiving, from a second computing device of the second user, a message for distribution; f. identifying, by a computer processor, the subscribers of the second user as recipients of the message; g. identifying, in the storage, the plurality of communication options selected by the first user; and h. sending the message to the subscribers of the second user, including the first user, wherein the sending includes sending the message to each of the plurality of communication options selected by the first user.",
    "2. The method of claim 1, wherein the second user is one of a plurality of users who are subscribers of the first user, and wherein the second user receives messages sent to subscribers of the first user, and wherein the plurality of communication options comprises e-mail, short messaging service (SMS), and web.",
    "3. The method of claim 1, further comprising:\na. receiving, from the first computing device, a registration request, requesting creation of a new account of the first user; b. creating the new account in response to receiving the registration request; and c. sending, to the first computing device, an acknowledgement message indicating that the new account is created, wherein the plurality of communication options is associated with the new account in the storage.",
    "4. The method of claim 1, further comprising:\na. receiving, from the first computing device, a request, requesting to join the plurality of users who are subscribers of the second user; and b. adding the first user to the subscribers of the second user in response to receiving the request.",
    "5. The method of claim 1, further comprising: receiving, from the first computing device of the first user, a configuration message comprising a plurality of message receipt preferences, wherein the sending of the message to the first user is based on the plurality of message receipt preferences.",
    "6. The method of claim 5, wherein the plurality of message receipt preferences comprises a time window for receiving messages, and wherein the method further comprises: making a determination that a current time is within the time window for receiving messages, wherein the sending of the message to the first user is based on the determination.",
    "7. The method of claim 1, further comprising:\na. identifying a hyperlink within the message; and b. displaying the hyperlink to the first user as an active link, wherein the active link comprises a shortened representation of the hyperlink.",
    "8. The method of claim 1, further comprising:\na. identifying, within the message, a reference to an image; and b. displaying, to the first user, the message with an indication of the image.",
    "9. A message distribution system, comprising:\na. a computer processor; b. a routing engine executing on the computer processor and configured to: receive, from a first computing device of a first user a selection of a plurality of communication options for receiving messages, wherein the first user is one of a plurality of users who are subscribers of a second user; c. store the selection of the plurality of communication options in a data repository; d. receive, from the first user, subscriber information indicative of one or more other users to be followed by the first user; e. store the subscriber information in the data repository; f. receive, from a second computing device of the second user, a message for distribution; g. identify the subscribers of the second user as recipients of the message; and h. identify, in the data repository, the plurality of communication options selected by the first user; and a transmission engine configured to send the message to the subscribers of the second user, including the first user, wherein the transmission engine sends the message to each of the plurality of communication options selected by the first user.",
    "10. The message distribution system of claim 9, wherein the second user is one of a plurality of users who are subscribers of the first user, and wherein the second user receives messages sent to subscribers of the first user.",
    "11. The message distribution system of claim 9, wherein the routing engine is further configured to:\na. receive, from the first computing device, a registration request, requesting creation of a new account of the first user; and b. create the new account in response to receiving the registration request, and wherein the transmission engine is further configured to send, to the first computing device, an acknowledgement message indicating that the new account is created wherein the plurality of communication options is associated with the new account in the data repository.",
    "12. The message distribution system of claim 11, wherein the routing engine is further configured to receive, from the first computing device, a request, requesting to join the plurality of users who are subscribers of the second user and wherein the message distribution system further comprises a group expansion module configured to: add the first user to the subscribers of the second user in response to receiving the request.",
    "13. The message distribution system of claim 9, wherein the message distribution system further comprises a rules module configured to: identify, for the first user, a plurality of message receipt preferences comprising a time window for receiving messages;\nand make a determination that a current time is within the time window for receiving messages, wherein the sending of the message to the first user is based on the determination.",
    "14. A non-transitory computer readable medium comprising a plurality of instructions for message distribution the plurality of instructions comprising functionality to:\na. receive, from a first computing device of a first user a selection of a plurality of communication options for receiving messages, wherein the first user is one of a plurality of users who are subscribers of a second user; b. store the selection of the plurality of communication options in a storage; c. receive, from the first user, subscriber information indicative of one or more other users to be followed by the first user; d. store the subscriber information in the data repository; e. receive, from a second computing device of the second user, a message for distribution; f. identify the subscribers of the second user as recipients of the message; g. identify, in the storage, the plurality of communication options selected by the first user; and h. send the message to the subscribers of the second user including the first user, wherein the sending includes sending the message to each of the plurality of communication options selected by first user."
